1.desc: It's time to discuss basic combat techniques!
1.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_1_NAME

10.desc: Your journey as a Summoner traveling across Grand Gaia has begun! Go forth, and don't forget what Tilith taught you!
10.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_10_NAME

100050.desc:
訪れた者の魂を晒し鍛えると言われる地。
そこには召喚師としての経験とカルマ獲得のチャンスが。
100050.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_100050_NAME

100051.desc:
訪れた者の魂を晒し鍛えると言われる地の深部。
そこには召喚師としての大きな経験とカルマ獲得のチャンスが。
100051.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_100051_NAME

100052.desc:
訪れた者の魂を晒し鍛えると言われる地の最深部。
そこには想像を絶する経験とカルマ獲得のチャンスが。
100052.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_100052_NAME

100053.desc:
訪れた者の魂を晒し極限まで鍛えると言われる地の隠し領域。
そこには想像を絶する経験とカルマ獲得の機会があるという。
100053.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_100053_NAME

100300.desc:
究極の力を引き出す神が祀られているという炎の神殿。
初心者立ち入るべからず。
100300.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_100300_NAME

100301.desc:
究極の力を引き出す神が祀られているという水の神殿。
初心者立ち入るべからず。
100301.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_100301_NAME

100302.desc:
究極の力を引き出す神が祀られているという樹の神殿。
初心者立ち入るべからず。
100302.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_100302_NAME

100303.desc:
究極の力を引き出す神が祀られているという雷の神殿。
初心者立ち入るべからず。
100303.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_100303_NAME

100304.desc:
究極の力を引き出す神が祀られているという神殿。
その最奥に神を越えるための力が眠っている。
100304.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_100304_NAME

100305.desc:
究極の力を引き出す神が祀られているという光の神殿。
初心者立ち入るべからず。
100305.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_100305_NAME

100306.desc:
究極の力を引き出す神が祀られているという闇の神殿。
初心者立ち入るべからず。
100306.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_100306_NAME

100900.area: Bearer of the Flaming God Arm
100900.dungeon: Bearer of the Flaming God Arm
100900.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_100900_NAME

100901.area: Bearer of the Flaming God Arm
100901.dungeon: Bearer of the Flaming God Arm
100901.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_100901_NAME

100902.area: Bearer of the Flaming God Arm
100902.dungeon: Bearer of the Flaming God Arm
100902.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_100902_NAME

100903.area: Bearer of the Flaming God Arm
100903.dungeon: Bearer of the Flaming God Arm
100903.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_100903_NAME

10200.desc: 目の前に広がる溶岩道に少しだけ心が怯む。これまでいくつもの難所を踏破してきたが、ここを進むには覚悟が必要だ。
10200.name: 熱道進軍

10201.desc: 炎の混じった竜の吐息が風に乗って流れてくる。近くに群れがいるに違いない。刺激しないように静かに進んでいこう。
10201.name: 炎竜のねぐら

10202.desc: ルジーナのように悪態をつきたくなるほどの暑さに辟易しながら先へと進む。肌がひりひりと痛むのは軽い火傷だろうか。
10202.name: 火の色

10203.desc: 溶岩の流れる音は、その見た目に反して意外と静かなものだ。そこに突如轟音が響き渡る。戦闘の準備をした方がいいだろう。
10203.name: 烈火の轟き

10204.desc: 地獄のような溶岩道もそろそろ終端らしい。しかし、敵が尽きる気配は無い。これも魔神の放った刺客なのだろうか？
10204.name: 溶岩溜り

10210.desc: 衝撃的な光景が目に飛び込む。赤い、赤い大海原が眼前に広がっていた。その色彩を前にして、ここが異界だと思い知る。
10210.name: 緋色の磯辺

10211.desc: 見た目に鮮やかな赤い海だが、その潮の香りは特別変わったものではない。視覚と嗅覚のずれが、強い違和感となって襲う。
10211.name: 赤き潮騒

10212.desc: 夕日に染まった赤い海を見たことは何度もあるが、そのことがかえって認識に不安定な歪みをもたらす。気分が悪くなってきた。
10212.name: 紅い海

10213.desc: モーラの言っていた魔神を寄せ付けぬほどの力を持つ六鎧というものが気になる。やはり戦わねばならないのだろうか。
10213.name: 浜辺の死闘

10214.desc: イシュグリアの海はどこも赤いのだろうか？そんなことを考えていると前方に敵の一団が現れた。ゆっくりしている暇は無い。
10214.name: 血色の波間

10220.desc: セリアも言っていたが、あまり研究所という雰囲気のしない場所だ。ただ、よく見ると所々に使途不明の装置が置かれている。
10220.name: 残された印

10221.desc: 廃墟と化した研究所は森に飲み込まれていた。無機質な壁に這う植物から、圧倒的な生命の力というものを感じてしまう。
10221.name: 森の侵蝕

10222.desc: これだけ植物に侵蝕されていながらも、施設の一部は生きているようだ。ここを作った科学力というのも相当なものだ。
10222.name: 枝葉の狭間

10223.desc: 場違いなほど濃厚な花の香りが漂ってくる。イシュグリアの植物が未知とはいえ、これは警戒した方が良さそうだ。
10223.name: 危険な香り

10224.desc: そろそろ研究所を抜けそうだが、パリスとルジーナがまだ合流していない。セリアとも別行動中だが、先へ進んでしまおう。
10224.name: 盾と矛

10230.desc: 天空から物凄い速度で召喚師に接近してきたその何かは、話し合いの余地も無いまま、攻撃態勢に入った。
10230.name: 危険な風

10231.desc: 強風が途切れることなく吹き荒れている。ひときわ大きな風車が重く響く風切り音と木材の軋む音を立てながら回っている。
10231.name: 天津風

10232.desc: 風が強いのはうっとうしいが、少なくとも暑かったり寒かったりするよりはましだろう。見たところ周囲に危険な様子もない。
10232.name: 烈風の道

10233.desc: 猛烈な突風に煽られ危うく転げそうになる。油断してはいけないここも決して易しい場所ではないようだ。気をつけよう。
10233.name: 突風警報

10234.desc: ここの風車も相当古いもののようだが、未だに朽ちることなく稼動している。もしかしたら研究所の動力の源なのだろうか？
10234.name: 強風力学

10240.desc: 召喚師の前に再び現れたベイオルグ。敗北する度に強くなる機能を備えているこの敵に対し、戦ってしまってもよいのだろうか？
10240.name: ベイオルグ再襲

10241.desc: 街並みを見る限り、魔神も人間と同じように生活していたことがわかる。それともここにも人間が住んでいたのだろうか？
10241.name: 寺院跡地

10242.desc: 坂の多い路地を抜けると大通りに行き当たった。しかし、これほど立派な街なのに、住人はどこへ行ってしまったのだろう？
10242.name: 極光大路

10243.desc: 大通りの角を曲がると、敵の一団が待ち受けていた。ここで襲ってくる敵は、この古都を守っている存在なのだろうか？
10243.name: 星読小路

10244.desc: 古都の外郭に近付いてきた。街を囲う防壁は、どんな素材を使っているのか、汚れ１つ無く白く輝いているように見える。
10244.name: 純白の城壁

10250.desc: この異様な階段を登りきれば、目的の古城にたどり着く。しかしこの長い長い階段を登って行くのは少しばかり憂鬱だ。
10250.name: 執拗な襲撃者

10251.desc: 階段は上にまだまだ続いている。オーンのことが気になるが、セリアやルジーナが話す通り、無事であることを願おう。
10251.name: 夜の帳

10252.desc: 延々と続く階段だというのに、敵はお構いなしに襲い掛かってくる。足を踏み外せば麓まで転がり落ちてしまうだろう。
10252.name: 漂う死臭

10253.desc: 場所柄、敵との交戦を避けることはできない。その上相手は常に高い位置から攻撃してくることになり、厳しい戦いが続く。
10253.name: 威圧の影

10254.desc: 城門が見えてきた。次の敵の波を越えれば古城に到着できるだろう。戦いの本番はそこからだが、手は抜けそうにない。
10254.name: 最終段に待ち受ける者

10260.desc: 目に付く機械類を破壊しながら進んでいく。カルがここにいる可能性があるらしいが、こんな場所で何をしているのだろうか。
10260.name: 機械化古城

10261.desc: 床や壁に張り巡らされた光の筋を見ていると、自分が巨大な機械の中に飲まれた気分になる。実際にそうなのかもしれないが。
10261.name: 回路走る中庭

10262.desc: 片っ端から装置を破壊しているが、どうにも手応えが無い。そもそも、この機械は何の役割を持っているのだろう？
10262.name: 配線の大広間

10263.desc: ベイオルグは体の大きさ自体が変わっていたそうだが、もしかしてこの城自体も取り込んでいるということはないだろうか。
10263.name: 歯車の玉座

10264.desc: そういえばベイオルグはどこへ行ったのだろう？モーラの言うようにここが重要な場所なら防衛に現れそうなものだが…
10264.name: 駆動する門扉

10265.desc: 手応えの無いまま城内を彷徨っていると、聞き覚えのある異音が響き渡った。やはりベイオルグがこっちに来るようだ！
10265.name: 不滅の兵器

10270.desc: 古城の裏手の崖を降りた先に広がる枯葉の森。ここにも魔神の影が現れるのだろうか。この地に魔神はいなかったはずだが…
10270.name: 滅びし醒神

11.desc: The calm grasslands keep on going.The monsters here are just right for a beginner.Keep moving forward.
11.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_11_NAME

12.desc: You can see a rocky mountain faintly on the horizon. Tilith is waiting at the "Cave of Flames" just beyond here.
12.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_12_NAME

2.desc: Memorize the strengths and weaknesses of each elements and how to trigger the Brave Burst!
2.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_2_NAME

20.desc: The magma flowing within this cave gives off an intense heat. The enemies in this cave have the power of fire.
20.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_20_NAME

200.desc: Your journey through Morgan begins in a huge desert. The scorching haze indicates the fierce battle to come.
200.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_200_NAME

20000.desc: Welcome to the newly discovered realm of Cordelica. A huge gate towers above you, as if it were beckoning Summoners inside...
20000.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_20000_NAME

20001.desc: Beyond the huge gate unfolds a fiery cave. It doesn’t look like you’ll find anything worthy of investigation here, so keep moving forward.
20001.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_20001_NAME

20002.desc: You’ve stumbled into a thriving monster habitat. Judging by the hungry glint in their eyes, you’re probably the first human they’ve seen in centuries.
20002.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_20002_NAME

20003.desc: There’s no respite from the scalding heat. A gust of hot wind blasting through the maze of caverns.
20003.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_20003_NAME

20004.desc: A cold wind dries the sweat from your forehead. Could the exit be nearby? You spot a shaft of light, but it’s guarded by a formidable-looking foe...
20004.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_20004_NAME

20010.desc: You exit the infernal cave and come upon a huge waterfall spanned by a breathtaking rainbow. Finally, some beautiful scenery to soothe your weary soul.
20010.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_20010_NAME

20011.desc: A monster ambush interrupts your reverie with the scenery. Dispose of them and continue with your investigation.
20011.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_20011_NAME

20012.desc: You pass behind the cascading waterfall and continue to the next area. Lugina’s warning plays in your mind, but you’re too curious to turn back now.
20012.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_20012_NAME

20013.desc: The roar of the waterfall cascading around you drowns out the sound of approaching demons. They lurk in the water and shadows, waiting for their moment to pounce.
20013.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_20013_NAME

20014.desc: Just as you’re about to exit on the other side of Ignia Falls, a watery monarch emerges from behind the waterfall. He’s come to expel the intruders in his domain...
20014.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_20014_NAME

20020.desc: On the other side of the huge waterfall a vast forest stretches as far as the eye can see. According to Lugina, the monsters here are the most dangerous you’ve faced.
20020.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_20020_NAME

20021.desc: The overgrown foliage deep inside the forest is maze-like in its complexity. What lies on the other side?
20021.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_20021_NAME

20022.desc: Even after the world has been reduced to rubble, the souls of bandits continue to exist deep within the forest. They target travelers’ valuables, just like when they were alive.
20022.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_20022_NAME

20023.desc: The bandits tell of a dragon who protects all the trees in the forest. Could that be where this distant roar is coming from?
20023.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_20023_NAME

20024.desc: A massive tree stretches into the heavens from the center of the forest. There's no chance of passing through the forest's twisting maze without its blessing.
20024.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_20024_NAME

20030.desc: Do as Lugina says and defeat the hordes of monsters dwelling within the fortress. You’ll be able to continue with your investigation afterwards.
20030.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_20030_NAME

20031.desc: Scores of monsters block your path forward, but there’s no turning back now. Show them who’s boss by attacking them head-on.
20031.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_20031_NAME

20032.desc: You break through the frontal defenses only to find yourself ambushed yet again, but this time from above! Time to quiet this raging beast.
20032.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_20032_NAME

20033.desc: Two monstrous birds, more ferocious than anything else you’ve encountered, lie in wait to stop the advance of any would-be intruders into their territory.
20033.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_20033_NAME

20034.desc: Danger awaits you in the great courtyard at the center of Valtan Fortress. Defeat whatever it is to complete Lugina's mission.
20034.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_20034_NAME

20040.desc: You arrive at the Tower of Light hot on the heels of Lugina and Paris. Could the mystery of Cordelic
20040.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_20040_NAME

201.desc: The bandits in this burning desert have much stronger resolve that those in Mistral, and it seems they intend to block your way.
201.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_201_NAME

202.desc: A summoned being known as the king of beasts is rampaging in the desert. A fierce battle with him is unavoidable.
202.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_202_NAME

203.desc: You've reached the desert's mid point. An incarnation of flames blocks the way, further scorching the land around it.
203.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_203_NAME

204.desc: The end of the desert is in view, and the wind now smells of the sea. However, a giant silhouette stands blocks your path...
204.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_204_NAME

21.desc: Continue deeper into the Cave of Flames. Beings who control fire are waiting ahead.
21.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_21_NAME

210.desc: You've reached the shore, escaping the desert. A calm, beautiful beach awaits you, but you must still be cautious.
210.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_210_NAME

211.desc: A huge ship is anchored on the beach. It's a pirate ship, and it seems there's no easy way past...
211.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_211_NAME

212.desc: The beautiful view continues, as do the number of enemies you encounter. Prepare yourself for a water assault.
212.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_212_NAME

213.desc: The end of the coastline is now in view. A Water Spirit is said to appear around here. How strong could it be?
213.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_213_NAME

214.desc: You've finally reached the coast's end. A dark forest is visible ahead, but surely something is lurking near...
214.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_214_NAME

22.desc: You've come far, but there's still no exit in site. There are supposed to be bandits in this area.
22.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_22_NAME

220.desc: Your eyes haven't adjusted to the dark since coming in from the coast. Are Karl and the others OK?
220.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_220_NAME

221.desc: Dark forests like this are usually full of bandits. Is it that they work better in the Dark? Either way, be careful.
221.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_221_NAME

222.desc: The discomfort you felt in the forests of Mistral is back, but this time it's worse. Could this be the work of a time mage?
222.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_222_NAME

223.desc: It's hard telling which trees are just trees and not just monsters in hiding. If only you could escape this forest...
223.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_223_NAME

224.desc: The darkness has lightened. The exit should be close, but there's tension in the air. Surely, the sign of a formidable foe.
224.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_224_NAME

23.desc: Looks like you'll be able to leave this cave soon, but there seems to be something sinister awaiting you at the end.
23.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_23_NAME

230.desc: After escaping the pitch black forest, you entered a vast wasteland. The area is being torn apart by lightning.
230.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_230_NAME

231.desc: You move forward as lightning strikes down all around you. Beware of incoming aerial attacks.
231.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_231_NAME

232.desc: You're nearing the center of the wastelands. Did Karl and his team successfully bring down the demon they were chasing?
232.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_232_NAME

233.desc: There's a temple barely visible in the distance. There's no sign of Karl, what has happened to him...
233.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_233_NAME

234.desc: A summoned thunder king is blocking the path at the end of the wasteland. You must defeat him before continuing.
234.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_234_NAME

240.desc: There is a temple bathed in light. Despite it being thousands of years old, it's as beautiful as the day it was built.
240.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_240_NAME

241.desc: You continue even deeper into the massive temple. You can make out the solemn silhouettes of pegasi standing about.
241.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_241_NAME

242.desc: You've nearly reached the middle of the temple. You can imagine the days when many would gather at this impressive alter.
242.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_242_NAME

243.desc: You can feel the enemies growing stronger the deeper you go. Unfortunately, the only way to the Tower of Morgan is forward.
243.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_243_NAME

244.desc: You reached the temple's innermost area. A mighty swordsman awaits you, and you can surely expect a fierce battle...
244.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_244_NAME

250.desc: You see ruins as you escape from the temple. It seems that whatever existed here before was destroyed by a great power.
250.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_250_NAME

251.desc: As you proceed, you realize the ruins cover a large area. It must have been a large city before.
251.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_251_NAME

252.desc: You've come to a plaza in the middle of the ruins. An enormous church embodies the former power of this devastated city.
252.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_252_NAME

253.desc: Leaving the church, you continue through the ruins. The temple was so beautifully preserved, what could've happened here?
253.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_253_NAME

254.desc: You reached the ruins' end. The majestic Tower of Morgan stands before you. However, a knight in thick armor awaits...
254.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_254_NAME

260.desc: Don't let Karl and Seria's wishes go to waste. Ascend the tower quickly and track down Abaddon and Graham!
260.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_260_NAME

261.desc: This tower is like a gigantic fortress. The spiral stairs that surround its vast outer walls are the only way up...
261.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_261_NAME

262.desc: Is this only the halfway point? You can still hear the cries from the fierce battle raging below... It's time to hurry.
262.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_262_NAME

263.desc: Past the halfway point, warriors summoned by Maxwell and Abaddon block the path. There's no turning back now.
263.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_263_NAME

264.desc: The Stairway to the Heavens has narrowed. You can no longer hear the shouts from the base. You're almost there.
264.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_264_NAME

265.desc: You've reached the top at last. Continue on and defeat Abaddon and Graham, you can't let Karl and the others down!
265.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_265_NAME

30.desc: You've emerged into a blizzard. It's so cold, watch out for enemies with water attacks.
30.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_30_NAME

300.desc: You're now in Maxwell's stronghold, St. Lamia. Many tall mountains are visible in the distance. The land looks rugged.
300.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_300_NAME

301.desc: Magma is gushing out all over, and it's scorching hot as far as the eye can see. Nothing could possibly live here.
301.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_301_NAME

302.desc: It's getting hotter and hotter as you near the mouth of the volcano. It's getting hard to even move...
302.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_302_NAME

303.desc: You finally made it through the pass. The intense heat hasn't gone, but at least it's all downhill from here. Hurry on ahead.
303.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_303_NAME

304.desc: Just as you were about to escape the volcano, it seems an undead beast is blocking your path...
304.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_304_NAME

31.desc: You are making progress, but the end of the snowscape still isn't visible. Don't forget to plan for water enemies.
31.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_31_NAME

310.desc: You've emerged from the base of a mountain. Now it's intensely cold, and it seems to be taking its toll on Tilith.
310.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_310_NAME

311.desc: Unlike the Volcano Eldent, this blizzard-covered sacred mountain has many steep cliffs. Watch your step.
311.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_311_NAME

312.desc: This place is also inhabitable. It's doubtful anyone could even last a minute around here. Hurry on ahead.
312.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_312_NAME

313.desc: Around the summit, stones are stacked in a alter-like pattern. Is this proof that the mountain was a place of worship?
313.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_313_NAME

314.desc: The summit is in sight, and you've spotted the altar. The end is near, but there are signs of a beast nearby...
314.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_314_NAME

32.desc: You've reached the center of the icy field. Beware, apparently there are pirates about on the ice...
32.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_32_NAME

320.desc: Beyond the sacred mountain lies the Blood Forest. Tilith is acting a bit odd, though, she might be sick...
320.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_320_NAME

321.desc: A sea of red surrounds you as you walk through this forest. The grass, the flowers, everythings red. What's the meaning of this?
321.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_321_NAME

322.desc: You continue deeper into the crimson forest. Suddenly, drops as red as blood fall down on you from the trees above.
322.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_322_NAME

323.desc: You feel your senses numbing as you're enveloped in a sea of red. It's probably not a good idea to stick around here.
323.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_323_NAME

324.desc: You've finally reached the end of the crimson forest. You see a color other than red and race towards it.
324.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_324_NAME

33.desc: The end of this cold snow field has come into view at last. However, it seems one of Maxwell's knights is waiting just ahead.
33.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_33_NAME

330.desc: You're halfway through St. Lamia, and Tilith's deteriorating condition has worsened. It's time to hurry.
330.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_330_NAME

331.desc: Mt. Wistorea is the steepest in the area, but its calm weather makes it the most comfortable environment so far.
331.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_331_NAME

332.desc: Hold off the hordes of giants as you move forward. You can't waste time with Tilith's current condition.
332.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_332_NAME

333.desc: The Thunderbird circles above, letting out a piercing cry. You've no choice but to confront it and take it down.
333.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_333_NAME

334.desc: You can make out St. Lamia Palace in the distance, but the roar of a beast from the foothills nearby are concerning...
334.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_334_NAME

340.desc: You come across a clearing bathed in a dazzling light, but as Tilith's curse is growing stronger there is no time to enjoy it.
340.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_340_NAME

341.desc: This area is obviously sacred, bathed in light and covered in green, but being so close to St. Lamia Palace surely strong foes await.
341.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_341_NAME

342.desc: Without provocation, hordes of shining demons swoop down on you. These demons must've been called upon by Maxwell...
342.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_342_NAME

343.desc: Seems even a holy goddess has been called on to block your path. However, you must defeat her and press on if you're to save Tilith.
343.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_343_NAME

344.desc: The exit is in sight, but a giant entity can be seen swooping down from the heavens, possibly to deliver your final trial...
344.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_344_NAME

350.desc: In a complete change of scenery, you come across a dark, rancid cave. Pass through this, and St. Lamia Palace awaits.
350.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_350_NAME

351.desc: This cave not only looks horrid, but is also full to the brim with fearsome beings. You mustn't lose focus here or else.
351.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_351_NAME

352.desc: There is a nagging chill in the air, though it isn't necessarily cold. Could it be this malicious air that surrounds you?
352.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_352_NAME

353.desc: It seems you've reached the dark, damp reaches of this hellish cave. Follow the wind to find your way out.
353.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_353_NAME

354.desc: You seem to have finally figured your way out of the cave, but all of the sudden an unsettling evil presence descends upon you...
354.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_354_NAME

360.desc: You've finally reached Maxwell's stronghold. You continue forward, having vowed to Tilith to destroy this depraved god.
360.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_360_NAME

361.desc: This castle once was revered for its majesty. While still impressive, it's surrounded in a sinister atmosphere.
361.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_361_NAME

362.desc: As expected, Maxwell has filled her base with incredibly powerful beings. Liberating them is going to be difficult.
362.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_362_NAME

363.desc: You've entered the castle's banquet hall. The sacred walls reek of wickedness, but you mustn't hesitate. Advance, for Tilith!
363.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_363_NAME

364.desc: You can feel the fallen god's presence grow stronger as you proceed. However, surely she has set up a powerful defensive line before her.
364.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_364_NAME

365.desc: At last, you've reached Maxwell. The battle to save Tilith and destroy the first of the four fallen gods begins now...
365.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_365_NAME

40.desc: Beyond the snow lie the forests that the sun doesn't reach. Beware, there are signs of monsters are all around.
40.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_40_NAME

41.desc: This monster-packed forest just goes on forever. Everything's the same, seems like you're walking in circles...
41.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_41_NAME

42.desc: It's said that bandits occupy this forest. They may be tough, but there's no way to avoid them.
42.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_42_NAME

43.desc: Dangerous hunters wielding longbows inhabit the depths of this forest, and they attack anyone who dares enter.
43.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_43_NAME

50.desc: Lightning occasionally roars throughout this damp land. It's quite unpleasant here. Prepare yourself for thunder.
50.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_50_NAME

5000007.desc: Moments after defeating the sealed god Lucius, Noel sends the Summoner on a mission along with Lugina. However, the demon they are after has the ability to reflect the souls of its opponents, unexpectedly drawing Lugina into a fierce battle with his doppe
5000007.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_5000007_NAME

5000010.desc:
神々との大戦の少し前、ラ・ヴェーダ共和国
に住む少女ミセルは、空より不思議な黒い物
体が落ちてくるのを目撃し、その黒い物体
ＤＵＥＬ‐ＧＸと遭遇する。
ＤＵＥＬ‐ＧＸが最近、近隣の村を滅ぼして
いる翼を持つ鎧“メルキオ”を追って異界よ
り現れたことを知った彼女は、さっそくメル
キオ討伐の旅に出発しようとするが……。
5000010.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_5000010_NAME

5008001.desc: The relics of Athensphere have yielded interesting results. Noel’s thirst for knowledge has the summoner searching for a particular figure in the memory gear…
5008001.name: The Tinkerer’s Deceit

51.desc: It looks to be a vast wetland. The terrain may prove more troublesome than the thunder-wielding enemies hiding in it.
51.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_51_NAME

52.desc: Seems there are bandits around here, too. They used to call the skies their own, but what strength that must've taken...
52.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_52_NAME

53.desc: At the end of these unpleasant wetlands the way is blocked by a former hero of Grand Gaia who was summoned by Maxwell.
53.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_53_NAME

60.desc: These ancient ruins have a solemn, holy air. It's much better than where you were before, but it's still ominous.
60.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_60_NAME

61.desc: It appears that a sage with the power of light is in the ruins. A guardian, perhaps?
61.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_61_NAME

62.desc: A shining, gallant white horse blocks the path. It defends its position, attacking mercilessly.
62.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_62_NAME

63.desc: A warrior of light lies in wait in the depths of these ruins, testing adventurers before they're allowed to pass.
63.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_63_NAME

70.desc: This spine-chillingly eerie mansion reeks of an evil presence. Here you'll need the power to oppose darkness.
70.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_70_NAME

71.desc: Light energy is strong against dark, but it's also its weakness. You must plan your strategy here carefully.
71.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_71_NAME

72.desc: A monster with snakes for arms has appeared. Beware, it seems many adventurers have been subdued by its strength.
72.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_72_NAME

73.desc: A grotesque swordsman awaits you, and you must overcome him in order to reach the Tower of Mistral.
73.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_73_NAME

81.desc: You've reached the Tower of Mistral at last. This is Maxwell's base inside Mistral. Hurry your way inside!
81.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_81_NAME

82.desc: This tower reaches amazingly high into the sky. Fearsome monsters await with blood-soaked claws.
82.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_82_NAME

83.desc: Halfway up, a giant flying dragon is defends the tower, attacking anyone who nears. You must avoid it's attacks to advance.
83.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_83_NAME

8311010.desc: Once a week, lunar shifts above affect the emotional spectrum of bulbs. The fields glow 255:0:0 from the emergence of Fire Bulbs, buzzed and excited.
8311010.name: Crimson Fields

8312010.desc: Once a week, lunar shifts above affect the emotional spectrum of bulbs. The fields turn humid from emergence of Water Bulbs, wet and soggy.
8312010.name: Misty Fields

8313010.desc: Once a week, lunar shifts above affect the emotional spectrum of bulbs. The fields shine from emergence of Earth Bulbs, lush and 0:255:0.
8313010.name: Moss Fields

8314010.desc: Once a week, lunar shifts above affect the emotional spectrum of bulbs. The fields shine from emergence of Thunder Bulbs, flashing with electric rhythm.
8314010.name: Static Fields

8315010.desc: Once a week, lunar shifts above affect the emotional spectrum of bulbs. The fields shine from emergence of Light Bulbs, bright and luminous.
8315010.name: Radiant Fields

8316010.desc: Once a week, lunar shifts above affects the emotional spectrum of bulbs. The fields emanate a purple glow from the emergence of Dark Bulbs, morbid and desolate.
8316010.name: Shadow Fields

84.desc: Masters of each of the four elements stand in wait as the final barrier in the path to the lord of the tower.
84.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_84_NAME

85.desc: You're almost at the top. A mechanical deity, likely Maxwell's creation, awaits. The final battle for Mistral begins.
85.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_85_NAME

90.desc: There is a mountain range at the end of the Egor Plains where it is said an evil god who once destroyed several small nations slumbers.
90.name: MST_DUNGEONS_MISSION_90_NAME
